# Nyx VM™ Trademark Policy

**Nyx VM™** is a trademark of **Surya Sekhar Roy**.

This document defines acceptable and prohibited uses of the Nyx VM trademark.

---

## 1. Trademark Ownership

The name **Nyx VM™** is claimed as a trademark by Surya Sekhar Roy.

The trademark identifies the official implementation of the Nyx Virtual
Machine runtime contained in the `nyx-vm` project.

All rights to the Nyx VM trademark are reserved.

---

## 2. Purpose of the Trademark

The Nyx VM trademark exists to ensure that users and developers can
reliably identify the official Nyx Virtual Machine implementation.

The trademark prevents confusion between the official Nyx VM project
and third-party or modified runtime implementations.

---

## 3. Permitted Uses

The Nyx VM trademark may be used in the following contexts.

### 3.1 Reference Use

You may reference Nyx VM in documentation, articles, tutorials,
research papers, or technical discussions.

Examples:

• "This runtime targets the **Nyx VM™**."
• "Programs compiled for **Nyx VM™** bytecode."

### 3.2 Compatibility Statements

Software may state compatibility with Nyx VM.

Examples:

• "Compatible with **Nyx VM™**."
• "Runs on the **Nyx VM™ runtime environment**."

Such statements must not imply endorsement or official affiliation.

### 3.3 Academic and Research Use

Universities, students, and researchers may reference Nyx VM in
academic publications or technical analysis.

---

## 4. Prohibited Uses

Without written permission from Surya Sekhar Roy, the Nyx VM trademark
may NOT be used for the following purposes.

### 4.1 Fork Branding

Forks or modified versions of the Nyx VM may not use the name
"Nyx VM" in their project name.

Examples:

Allowed:

MyRuntime (fork of Nyx VM)

Not allowed:

Nyx VM Fork
Nyx VM Enhanced
Nyx VM Community Edition

### 4.2 Competing Runtime Branding

The Nyx VM trademark may not be used to name or promote competing
virtual machine runtimes or execution engines.

Examples of prohibited names:

Nyx VM Pro
Nyx VM Enterprise
Nyx VM Cloud Runtime

### 4.3 Commercial Branding

Companies may not use the Nyx VM trademark for product names,
services, or marketing without written permission.

### 4.4 Misleading Representation

You may not imply that a project is the official Nyx VM project
if it is not maintained by the trademark owner.

---

## 5. Official Nyx VM Project Identification

The official Nyx VM project may identify itself using statements such as:

Official Nyx VM™ Project
Maintained by Surya Sekhar Roy

Only the official project maintained by Surya Sekhar Roy may use
this designation.

---

## 6. Trademark Symbol

The ™ symbol indicates a claimed trademark.

Examples:

Nyx VM™
Nyx Virtual Machine™

The trademark may later become a registered trademark.

---

## 7. Permission Requests

Requests to use the Nyx VM trademark for commercial purposes
or branding must be submitted to the trademark owner.

Requests should include:

• the intended use
• the product or service name
• distribution details.

---

## 8. Changes to This Policy

This trademark policy may be updated or modified by the author
to protect the integrity of the Nyx VM project.

---

## 9. Summary

You may:

✔ reference Nyx VM in documentation or research
✔ state compatibility with Nyx VM
✔ build software that runs on Nyx VM

You may not:

✘ present modified runtimes as Nyx VM
✘ use Nyx VM as branding for forks
✘ create products using the Nyx VM name without permission

